div.p:
When asked for a breakdown of sources of imports to demonstrate
                                    the difficulties that may arise, de Margerie submitted later the
                                    followg: 


                                            Wheat
                                            —85 percent from US;




                                            15 percent from
                                                Argentina;



                                            Fats and Oils
                                            —50 percent from US;




                                            50 percent from
                                                Philippines;



                                            Coal
                                            —88 percent from US;




                                            12 percent from
                                                Ruhr;



                                            Petroleum
                                            —35 percent from US:




                                            40 percent from
                                                Venezuela;




                                            25 percent from Middle
                                                East;



                                            Fertilizer
                                            —60 percent from US;




                                            40 percent from
                                                Chile.
